<p>The big issue I see here is having a driver station connection is not the same as having a dashboard connection. They run on completely separate unrelated protocols, and having one in no way guarantees you have the other.</p>","post_number":6,"post_type":1,"posts_count":12,"updated_at":"2023-03-19T16:16:59.143Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":125,"readers_count":124,"score":25.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":430824,"topic_slug":"hold-robotinit-until-driver-station-data-arrives","display_username":"Thad House","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":16147,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"WPILib Dev | 2025 VOTY"},"post_url":"/t/hold-robotinit-until-driver-station-data-arrives/430824/6","custom_user_title":"WPILib Dev | 2025 VOTY","reactions":[{"id":"point_up","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3167863,"name":"Thad House","username":"Thad_House","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/t/a4c791/{size}.png","created_at":"2023-03-19T16:30:10.193Z","cooked":"<pre><code class="lang-auto">int handle = WPIUtilJNI.createEvent(false, false);
DriverStationJNI.provideNewDataEventHandle(handle);
try {
  WPIUtilJNI.waitForObject(handle);
} catch (InterruptedException e) {
  Thread.currentThread().interrupt();
}
DriverStationJNI.removeNewDataEventHandle(handle);
WPIUtilJNI.destroyEvent(handle);
</code></pre>
<p>Thats the code to do that this year. We don‚Äôt have a high level way to do it this year, its all JNI This does mean its technically unsupported, and we can break it even in mid season updates (Although this is generally unlikely). The plan is to add a high level method back again next year, but for a different purpose.</p>","post_number":7,"post_type":1,"posts_count":12,"updated_at":"2023-03-19T16:31:57.084Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":117,"readers_count":116,"score":48.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":430824,"topic_slug":"hold-robotinit-until-driver-station-data-arrives","display_username":"Thad House","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":16147,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"WPILib Dev | 2025 VOTY"},"post_url":"/t/hold-robotinit-until-driver-station-data-arrives/430824/7","custom_user_title":"WPILib Dev | 2025 VOTY","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3250427,"name":"Alexander Hamilton","username":"GalexY","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/galexy/{size}/200203_2.png","created_at":"2023-11-07T05:49:49.129Z","cooked":"<p>Another method that 1622 recommends is doing a straight while loop in the initialization of your robotContainer (or directly in robotInit) which does the following:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-java">while (DriverStation.getAlliance() == Alliance.Invalid) {
    DriverStation.refreshData();
}
// Cache our alliance to a variable
this.alliance = DriverStation.getAlliance();
</code></pre>
<p>but I was always concerned with having a while loop in any part of robot code. At least we don‚Äôt tell FMS that the robot code is ready until it‚Äôs done, and I was told that it is safe to use this code, though I can‚Äôt tell if it has worked for us or not. I was also told that Alliance.Invalid is not ever used in WPIlib though it is indeed a variable in the code, so that is worth mentioning as well.</p>","post_number":8,"post_type":1,"posts_count":12,"updated_at":"2023-11-07T05:50:04.040Z","reply_count":2,"reply_to_post_number":7,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":94,"readers_count":93,"score":38.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":430824,"topic_slug":"hold-robotinit-until-driver-station-data-arrives","display_username":"Alexander Hamilton","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":16147,"username":"Thad_House","name":"Thad House","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/t/a4c791/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":54288,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"4738 Programming Lead | Driver ü¶í"},"post_url":"/t/hold-robotinit-until-driver-station-data-arrives/430824/8","custom_user_title":"4738 Programming Lead | Driver ü¶í","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3250429,"name":"Alexander Hamilton","username":"GalexY","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/galexy/{size}/200203_2.png","created_at"